<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="3d787d59-1fdb-45b4-8bc1-f1021b20a7d8" >

    <h3><em>How will I be paid?</em></h3> 
<p>In order to get paid, timesheets need to be submitted by employees and approved by their supervisors/leaders or their assigned delegates. Please refer to the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/content/ryerson/hr/employee-resources/cupe-3904-3/ta-ga-lab-monitors-invigilators/pay-info/pay-schedule/index.html">pay deadlines</a>&nbsp;schedule.</p> 
<p>If you have not submitted any hours for your existing contracts, because your hours are pre-established, then you do not need to worry about inputting your hours. You will receive appropriate payment without the submission of timesheets.<br> </p> 
<h3><em>How will I be assigned alternate work?</em></h3> 
<p>In working with your supervisor, you may be asked to do other duties that are appropriate based on your qualifications and in accordance with collective agreement provisions, if applicable. For example, a lab monitor may be asked to do online invigilation. Your supervisor will reach out to you with remote working options. Subject to prior approval by your supervisor, if you assume alternate duties and this results in working more hours than the contract amount you will be paid for these additional hours.</p> 
<p>Your supervisor will inform your department subsequently to revise your contract and add the additional hours so you will be paid accordingly.</p>
    





</div>
